## Frequently Asked Questions

### General Questions

**Q: What is the difference between a psychiatrist and a therapist?**
A: A psychiatrist is a medical doctor (MD) who can prescribe medication and provide medical treatment for mental health conditions. A therapist provides talk therapy and counseling but cannot prescribe medication. Empathy Health Clinic offers both services for comprehensive care.

**Q: Do you accept new patients?**
A: Yes, we are actively accepting new patients and typically offer same-week appointments. Visit https://empathyhealthclinic.com/new-patients to get started.

**Q: Do you offer telehealth appointments?**
A: Yes, we offer virtual therapy and telepsychiatry appointments throughout Florida. Our online services are covered by most insurance plans at the same rate as in-person visits.

### Cost Questions

**Q: How much does a psychiatrist cost in Orlando?**
A: With insurance, initial evaluations typically have a copay of $20-$60. Without insurance, initial psychiatric evaluations range from $250-$400, and follow-up medication management visits cost $100-$200.

**Q: Do you offer payment plans?**
A: Yes, we offer affordable payment options and sliding scale fees for qualifying patients. See our pricing page for details.

### Insurance Questions

**Q: What insurance do you accept?**
A: We accept Cigna, Aetna, United Healthcare, Blue Cross Blue Shield, UMR, Medicare, Medicaid, Oscar Health, Tricare, and Sunshine Health.

**Q: Do you accept Medicare?**
A: Yes, we accept Medicare for both psychiatry and therapy services.

**Q: Do you accept Medicaid?**
A: Yes, we accept Medicaid for mental health services.

### Appointment Questions

**Q: How do I schedule an appointment?**
A: Call (386) 848-8751 or visit https://empathyhealthclinic.com/request-appointment to schedule online.

**Q: How long is the first appointment?**
A: Initial psychiatric evaluations typically last 45-60 minutes. First therapy sessions are usually 50-60 minutes.

**Q: Can I get a same-day appointment?**
A: We offer same-day and same-week appointments for urgent needs. Call our office for availability.

### Treatment Questions

**Q: What conditions do you treat?**
A: We treat anxiety disorders, depression, ADHD, bipolar disorder, PTSD, OCD, insomnia, schizophrenia, and other mental health conditions. See https://empathyhealthclinic.com/what-we-treat for details.

**Q: Do you prescribe medication for ADHD?**
A: Yes, our psychiatrists can prescribe ADHD medications after a comprehensive evaluation.

**Q: Do you offer EMDR therapy?**
A: Yes, we offer EMDR (Eye Movement Desensitization and Reprocessing) for trauma and PTSD treatment.
